article(data-role='home')
  h1 Creative <em>&</em> Pure
  p A CSS framework for 
    a(href='https://www.meteor.com/', target='_blank') Meteor
  p It provides a set of re-usable widgets from 
    a(href='http://tympanus.net/codrops/', target='_blank') Codrops
    |  articles, all created using 
    a(href='http://stylus-lang.com/', target='_blank') Stylus.

article(data-role='usage')
  h1: a(href='#usage') Usage
  p Add it as a regular package.
  pre: code.bash.
    meteor add pierreeric:creativepure
  p We recommend using the following additional packages:
  pre: code.bash.
    meteor add coffeescript mquandalle:jade mquandalle:stylus fortawesome:fontawesome
  p We now set some global variables in a Stylus file.
  pre: code.stylus.
    // Base path for Creative & Pure
    basePath = '.meteor/local/build/programs/web.browser/packages/pierreeric_creativepure/styles/%s'

    // Global variables
    roundCorner =     3px
    buttonSmallSize = 70px

    // Main colors
    brandColor =    #dd7c27
    textColor =     darken(brandColor, 70%)
    bgColor =       lighten(brandColor, 90%)
    brandPrimary =  brandColor
    brandDanger =   hsl(0, saturation(brandColor),lightness(brandColor))
    brandWarning =  hsl(45, saturation(brandColor),lightness(brandColor))
    brandSuccess =  hsl(120, saturation(brandColor),lightness(brandColor))
    brandInfo =     hsl(240, saturation(brandColor),lightness(brandColor))

    // Breakpoints using Rupture
    maxSize = 960px
    rupture.scale = 0 600px 800px maxSize
    rupture.scale-names = 'small' 'medium' 'desktop' 'hd'

    // Fonts for Typographic
    monoFont = optima
    fontSize()
      font-size 11px
      +above('small')
        font-size @font-size + 1
      +above('medium')
        font-size @font-size + 2
      +above('desktop')
        font-size @font-size + 3
      +above('hd')
        font-size @font-size + 4

    // Default transition values
    defaultTransitionValue = .3s ease-out
  p And we are ready to GO.
  +link
  +textInput
